data.title: Good food
data.text: Cheng Garden is the #1 take out Chinese for my husband and I. They deliver or you can dine in and also take out. The food tastes really good and even with delivery it is hot when you get it. As with all delivery make sure you have your order right before you hang up but if they get it wrong, they are willing to correct it. I don't order Chinese take out from any other restaurant in town.

data.title: Above-average Chinese delivery
data.text: Feeling lazy? Order Cheng's Chinese. Check out the pictures of the amount of food you get. I ordered the pu-pu  platter and sweet and sour chicken with pork fried rice and a shrimp egg roll. Everything was good. I was surprised at the content of the pu-pu platter. It had shrimp, chicken, two types of egg rolls, pork strips, teriyaki chicken, on a stick, fried wontons and crab rangoon. Again, look at the pictures. It is very good. I will be ordering again next time I'm feeling lazy.

data.title: Good food, friendly staff
data.text: Nice meal, not fancy but good hot food. The wonton soup was excellent, flavorful broth with lots of wontons. Generals chicken was good, large serving with crispy chicken. Excellent steamed dumplings, large and filled well. The crab Rangoon was not as sweet as some that I have had but they were crispy and good. Not fancy, plastic dinnerware and Styrofoam plates and cups. This place does a lot of take out but they do have a fairly large seating area also. I would go back if in the area.

data.title: Food is "usually" good not consistent - horrible customer service
data.text:
We order delivery from here usually 1 to 2 times a week.  Food is "usually" good, but last time my order was horribly over cooked and one person ordered white rice and got fried rice with pork.  This person can't eat pork!  I faxed them a note about the problem and asked they comp orders the following week for the 2 bad items and NEVER heard back!

Also previously, my order was incorrect and I called to tell them and the lady who answered wanted to argue with me.  She also should not answer the phone, she has horrible customer service skills.
